nd Cainan was the father of Shelah,"}], "25": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 48, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 10}, "marker": "k", "text": "Peleg means division ."}], "4": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 74, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 12}, "marker": "a", "text": "SP and some MT manuscripts (see also LXX and 1 Chronicles 1:7); most MT manuscripts Dodanites"}], "7": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 40, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 7}, "marker": "b", "text": "Sabtah is a variant of Sabta ; see 1 Chronicles 1:9."}], "8": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 59, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 13}, "marker": "c", "text": "Or who established himself as a mighty warrior or who became the first fearless leader"}], "9": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 29, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 6}, "marker": "d", "text": "Or in defiance of ; twice in this verse"}]}, "11": {"13": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 104, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 19}, "marker": "d", "text": "Hebrew; LXX (see also Luke 3:35–36) 12When Arphaxad was 135 years old, he became the father of Cainan. 13And after he had become the father of Cainan, Arphaxad lived 430 years and had other sons and daughters, and then he died. When Cainan had lived 130 years, he became the father of Shelah. And after he had become the father of Shelah, Cainan lived 330 years and had other sons and daughters. Note that LXX also adds 100 years to the ages of Shelah, Eber, Peleg, Reu, Serug, and Nahor in this genealogy."}], "2": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 33, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 5}, "marker": "a", "text": "Or from the east or in the east"}, {"anchor": {"anchor_index": 2, "char_offset": 74, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 14}, "marker": "b", "text": "That is, Babylonia"}], "9": [{"anchor": {"anchor_index": 1, "char_offset": 31, "scope": "verse", "word_index": 7}, "marker": "c", "text": "Or Babylon ; the Heb